Rating: 3
I used a mixture of fish: Bass, Pickeral and Crappy (Waleye for my neighbours in the south). It was fresh that my partner caught and frozen for a few months. I don't have a food processor so I cut everything as small as possible. I added half a jalepeno because I like some bite. I didn't have parsley but did add a bit of fresh chives. It turned out great and I served it with tartar sauce. My stepson who will not eat fish even liked it. I suppose because it was fried! I will use this as a camping recipe. It is great for the mini fish the kids catch!

Rating: 4
This is excellent, at least the way I did it. Listening to the other reviewers who said it was bland, I made a fine mince of onion, a mild Fresno red pepper and celery, which I sweated until soft in olive. I did the bread crumbs and cod in the food processor, then stirred in the onion mixture, added parsley, egg, cayenne pepper and enough breadcrumbs so it would bind together. I dredged the patties in a LOT of breadcrumbs and let them sit in the fridge for two hours to firm up. Fried in peanut oil. They browned beautifully. Served with tartar sauce made with Hellman's mayo, a minced cornichon, capers, parsley and a squirt of lemon juice. Really good. If you pre- saute or sweat the veggies, it makes everything more tasty.

