Rating: 3
I've made this recipe many times and along the way tweaked it a bit so that it's perfect for us. (1) substituted chopped onion for the scallions; (2) used a full cup of fresh crumbs, not a scant cup, for the fish cakes; (3) made them early in the day or several hours before frying; (4) cooked them all at once in a 12-inch skillet until really browned on both sides and (5) served them with a good tarter sauce. If you're near a Wegmans, try their brand. We love these.

