Rating: 3
These cakes have a nice fresh flavor, but I agree with other cooks that they are kind of bland. I served them with a yogurt, capers, and horseradish sauce. As recommended, I added 1 tsp. Old Bay, which could have even been 1 1/2 tsp next time. I also added 1/2 a green pepper and 1 clove of garlic, and even with these additions, I still wished they had a little extra something. I think using seasoned breadcrumbs would definitely be an improvement, and will do that next time. Also, be sure to refrigerate for at least 15 minutes, as mine were falling apart in the pan, and i think it's best to flatten them out once they're in the pan. Overall, though, a nice alternative to richer fish cakes and a nice change for a weeknight meal.

Rating: 4
I was very impressed by these codfish cakes. They were delicious and crisp. I followed the recipe exactly except that I added a tiny bit more salt and about 1/4 teaspoon of Old Bay Seasonings. I didn't want the seasonings to overpower the fish and bread. I sauteed them in a preheated Look Saute pan over medium heat until golden brown and crisp on each side then served with a small amount of tartar sauce. My cod was frozen and not completely thawed when I cut it into chunks and briefly processed in the food processer. I made a little extra bread crumbs for breading because of the moisture in the fish mixture. They turned out very light, and crisp. We are certainly looking forward to making this recipe again.

Rating: 3
I've made this twice now. The first time as written and it was a little bland as others have commented. This time I added some fennel because I had it on hand, some garlic because I like garlic, some anchovies and some Old Bay. A little too much Old Bay this time so I'll try a tsp next time. The cakes were perked up from these additions. I think this recipe has possibilities with some more tinkering.

Rating: 2
I liked the fresh, light taste, but I found these to be a little bland. Next time I'll use seasoned breadcrumbs instead of making my own, and add some dry mustard and maybe paprika to the fish mixture. I subsituted half a green bell pepper for the celery, which kept the crunchiness but (I think) gave it a little more flavor.

